headline: Nike’s Costco Dunk Drop Tests Brand Reset And Investor Patience
summary: Nike (NYSE:NKE) has kicked off a brand reset built around tighter product scarcity and fewer promotions. A surprise Kirkland Signature x Nike SB Dunk Low release at Costco quietly rolled out and quickly attracted heavy attention. The collaboration is being watched as an early signal of how Nike plans to rebuild hype and exclusivity around its footwear franchises. Nike shares recently closed at $65.55, with the stock up 5.1% over the past week and 1.8% over the past month. Over longer...
